rComments: "What?? What did he just say???" comprises much of what you will be asking yourself during lecture. Honestly, if he didn't have such a thick accent, he might have been a good professor. His exams are relatively easy.

I could NOT understand him at all. He has a thick accent, and no one knew when he was asking a question. He is obsessed with Papayas, and only talks about them. He is really nice, but just not who I wanted to teach me genetics.
HIS portion of genetics is really easy but the second half (with a different professor) is much worse and way more boring. He loves to talk about papayas and relate them to lecture
